    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9557" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χάζομαι</span></b> , subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαζώμἑσ̓θ</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">α</span>),
          imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χάζεο</span>, ipf. (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐ</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χάζετ</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ο</span>), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-οντ</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ο</span>), fut.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χάσσονται</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χάσσατ</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ο</span>),
          inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-ασθαι</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-άμενος</span>, aor. red. part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεκαδών</span>, mid. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεκάδοντο</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">give way, fall back, retire</span>
          before some one, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄψ, ὀπίσω</span>, and w.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὑπό,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 4.497</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            φράζεο καὶ χάζεο</span>, ‘bethink and shrink,” <i><span class="en">Il. 5.440</span></i>; then with gen., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">give
            over, rest from</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μάχης, δουρός, Ο
            426</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.539</span></i>. Here
          belongs the causative <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεκαδών</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">depriving</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            11.334</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 21.153</span></i>, 170,
          unless this form should be referred to <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κήδω</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
